 A special election was held June 28, 1960, to fill the seat vacated by [[William Langer]], who died November 8, 1959. [[Clarence Norman Brunsdale]], a former [[Governor of North Dakota]], was temporarily appointed to the seat on November 19 of that year until the [[special election]] was held. [[North Dakota Democratic-NPL Party]] candidate [[Quentin N. Burdick]] faced [[North Dakota Republican Party|Republican]] [[John E. Davis (North Dakota politician)|John E. Davis]] for election to the seat. Davis had been serving as Governor of the state since 1957.<ref>{{Cite web |date=June 28, 1960 |title=Our Campaigns - ND US Senate Special Election Race |url=http://www.ourcampaigns.com/RaceDetail.html?RaceID=144709}}</ref>

