 ==Primary elections==
 The primary elections were originally scheduled for April 4, 2020. On March 13, they were moved to June 20 due to concerns over the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United States|COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/13/louisiana-postpones-democratic-primary-over-coronavirus-the-first-state-to-do-so.html|title=Louisiana postpones Democratic primary over coronavirus, the first state to do so|work=CNBC|date=March 13, 2020}}</ref> Then on April 14, they were further pushed back to July 11.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Health/wireStory/louisiana-presidential-primary-pushed-back-july-11-70147344|title=Louisiana presidential primary pushed back again, to July 11|work=ABC News|date=April 14, 2020}}</ref>

 ===Republican primary===
 Incumbent President [[Donald Trump]] was essentially uncontested in the Republican primary.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/2b1c648f10f81d6d56dc7425b6c0f0b3|title=Donald Trump, Joe Biden win Louisiana's presidential primary|website=Associated Press|date=July 11, 2020}}</ref> The state has 46 delegates to the [[2020 Republican National Convention]].<ref name="GP-GOP">{{cite web|title=Louisiana Republican Delegation 2020|url=https://www.thegreenpapers.com/P20/LA-R|publisher=The Green Papers|accessdate=June 23, 2020}}</ref>

